    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.22.21b" />
                
            <opener>    
                
                <dateline>Monday, 11-10-'58</dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
            </opener>
                <p>I'm wondering if you may be sick, or if a letter was lost here.</p>
                
                <p>Bob Kelly died several days before election. He was <del/> running for state auditor. A fine man, and a friend.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Affectionate thoughts for <hi rend="underline">each</hi> of you and all of you together.</salute>
                
                <signed>John</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript><p>I'm in <hi rend="underline">Jed Smith</hi>. It is going better than I could have expected.</p>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                    
                  <pb facs="nei.j4c.22.21a"/>
                <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                
<gap reason="missing"/>


                <p>the great old and lamented Boston Transcript. His long article on <hi rend="underline">Glass</hi> was the best that appeared. He is still living. Only recently he issued some anthology: If you should write him, asking him to comment on the matter, I believe you would get something you could use, &#8212; <del/>something of the "time-mood" that can carry over only through personal reminiscience. You'd know how to express your desire.</p></postscript>   
                

            </div1>
        </body>
        
